data.title: Alix Earle Photos, News, and Videos
data.text:
Alix Earle spilled on her love life after a year full of relationship drama.

The 23-year-old TikTok star was linked to Tyler Wade in late 2022 before she started dating her current boyfriend Braxton Berrios.

Both relationships sparked drama online, and she decided to share her side of the story during the newest episode of her Hot Mess podcast.

Read more for Alix Earle’s side of the story… More Here! »

Chris Olsen and Dylan Mulvaney were among the social stars who stepped out at Heidi Klum‘s annual Halloween bash held at Marquee on Tuesday night (October 31) in New York City.

The TikTokers were joined on the carpet in matching costumes with their plus ones, both pulling from popular movies.

Chris and boyfriend Patrick Johnson made their red carpet debut as a couple as Ken and Alan from the Barbie movie. Dylan was joined by Lily Drew as they dressed up as Romy and Michele from Romy and Michele’s High School Reunion.

Hours ahead of the party, Chris uploaded a cute TikTok with Patrick in their outfits.

“The love story no one knew they needed @Patrick Johnson #ken #allen #barbie,” he captioned the video. Check it out below!

Other influencers who stepped out at the party were an unrecognizable Alix Earle, dressed as Jadis the White Witch from The Chronicles of Narnia, James Charles, Eva Gutowski, Charly Jordan, Elevator Boys, Emma Norton, Meredith Duxbury and Brandon Remer, and Brigitte Pheloung with Lauren Wolfe.

@chris The love story no one knew they needed @Patrick Johnson #ken #allen #barbie ♬ original sound – Chris Olsen

Check out more photos of the influencers at Heidi Klum’s Halloween party in the gallery…

Alix Earle is speaking out about the controversy surrounding her relationship with NFL player Braxton Berrios.

The 22-year-old TikTok star and the 27-year-old NFL wide receiver have been dating for a few months, and even hit the red carpet together at the ESPYs back in July.

However, after his ex Sophia Culpo said he cheated on her, many accused Alix of being the one he cheated with and called her a homewrecker.

Now, Alix is speaking out and addressing the accusations on the latest episode of Alex Cooper‘s Call Her Daddy podcast.

Find out what she said inside… More Here! »

Is Alix Earle headed to the world of reality television with her family?!

The 22-year-old content creator is addressing the possibility that her and her family will be starring in their own reality show, ala The Kardashians or The D’Amelio Show, in a new interview.

If you didn’t know, Alix is launching a new show, but it’s a podcast through her deal with The Unwell Network, about her life and according to her, it will be like “I am talking to a friend or I am on FaceTime with a friend.”

“A lot of people have said to me that they think I should do a reality TV show or they want to see more of my life,” she tells WSJ Magazine. “I feel like this podcast is going to be a way for me to produce a show of my own.”

But does this mean there’s also room for a reality show surrounding her and her family??

Find out what she revealed inside… More Here! »

Influencers are starting to take over New York Fashion Week!

Alix Earle, Davis Burleson and Tessa Brooks were among those stepping out for the Victoria’s Secret The Tour ‘23 event kicking off NYFW on Wednesday (September 6) at The Manhattan Center in New York City.

More influencers in attendance included Stassie Karanikolaou, Alex Consani, Olivia Ponton and Meredith Duxbury.

Also stepping out were models Gigi Hadid, Amelia Gray, Iris Law, Alton Mason and Lila Moss, tennis star Naomi Osaka, actors AnnaSophia Robb and Stefania LaVie Owen, who played sisters in The Carrie Diaries, Lukas Gage and Drew Ray Tanner, and singers Kylie Cantrall, Renee Rapp, Faouzia, Grace VanderWaal and Doja Cat.

Victoria’s Secret The Tour is a reimagined fashion show, celebrating women and global creatives, taking audiences “on a journey through the behind-the-scenes craft and intimate stories of the VS20 – a group of twenty innovative global creatives who will conceive four fashion curations from the vibrant cities of Bogota, Lagos, London and Tokyo, alongside iconic custom Victoria’s Secret designs.”
